The paper focuses on improving neural network architecture search, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the use of differentiable architecture search (DARTS), which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper proposes a new search space representation, which could potentially fall under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR).
